o reconsider the origins of the system of gender relations that has dominated American culture for two hundred years.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEthicsxHistoryxUnited States. 0aEthicszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aSex rolexHistoryxUnited States. 0aSex rolezUnited StatesxHistory. 0aWomen colonistsxHistoryxUnited States. 0aWomen colonistszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aWomenxHistoryxUnited States. 0aWomenzUnited StatesxHistory. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093647840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520936478423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520936478/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles